text.section:
Income tax is not required to be withheld at the time wages are paid to a nonresident:
for State income tax withholding purposes, if the Comptroller and the state in which the nonresident resides have agreed in writing to allow a reciprocal exemption from tax and withholding for the wages of residents of each state that are earned in the other state;
for county income tax withholding purposes, if:
the nonresident derives wages from employment in a county; and
the Comptroller determines that each locality in which the nonresident resides:
for tips, to the extent that the amount required to be withheld on the tips causes the total withholdings for the period to exceed the available net wages other than tips after deductions are made for:
the federal income and Social Security taxes and income tax required to be withheld on wages other than tips; and
the federal income and Social Security taxes required to be withheld on the tips; or
if the wages are paid to an individual rendering police, fire, rescue, or emergency services in an area covered under a state of emergency declared by the Governor under § 14-107 of the Public Safety Article by:
a nonprofit organization not registered to do business in the State and not otherwise doing business in the State; or
a state, county, or political subdivision of a state, other than the State of Maryland.
